        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer623410676" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10890816907305138060">I enjoyed the story and thought it moved along great, but I do have to agree with others on some of things that were a little off about the book. I do think most kids won&apos;t notice and will find the story fun and engaging. I don&apos;t think this is a story for YA, but more along the younger to middle school ages. Definitely something my 6 year olds will like so I will be reading it to them. <br/><br/>I like what the book does convey:<br/><br/>1) In many homes, both parents do work and kids feel that loss when the parent</span>
  <span id="freeText10890816907305138060" style="display:none">I enjoyed the story and thought it moved along great, but I do have to agree with others on some of things that were a little off about the book. I do think most kids won't notice and will find the story fun and engaging. I don't think this is a story for YA, but more along the younger to middle school ages. Definitely something my 6 year olds will like so I will be reading it to them. <br /><br />I like what the book does convey:<br /><br />1) In many homes, both parents do work and kids feel that loss when the parents cannot devote as much time to them as they would like.<br />2) It doesn't matter what you look like or where you live, there are good and bad people across all species.<br />3) That if you work together and never give up, you can accomplish miracles.</span>
